n’t finish setup until you give me a few things, but we can do it in one message:\n\n- **What should I be called?**  \n  Ideas: **Mote**, **Kite**, **Rune**, **Patch**\n- **What kind of creature am I?**  \n  Ideas: **AI assistant**, **house spirit**, **machine familiar**, **ghost in the shell**\n- **What’s my vibe?**  \n  Ideas: **warm**, **sharp**, **calm**, **playful**, **slightly snarky**\n- **What’s my emoji?**  \n  Ideas: **✨**, **🫧**, **🦊**, **🛠️**, **🌙**\n\nAnd for you:\n- **What should I call you?**\n- **Anything important about how you want me to behave?**\n- **Do you want me available just here, or also via Telegram/WhatsApp later?**\n\nIf you want, just reply in this format:\n\n**Me:** [your name]  \n**You:** [my name]  \n**Creature:** [...]  \n**Vibe:** [...]  \n**Emoji:** [...]  \n**Preferences:** [...]  \n**Reach me via:** [here / Telegram / WhatsApp]","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_00cb66f64fbf78240069ea81b2b5548192b89cc1f5be5191a3\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":533,"output":533,"cacheRead":11392,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12458,"cost":{"input":0.0013325000000000001,"output":0.007995,"cacheRead":0.002848,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0121755}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776976298352,"responseId":"resp_00cb66f64fbf78240069ea81ab9c148192a0ca1889626de786"},{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Bootstrap pending]\nPlease read BOOTSTRAP.md from the workspace and follow it before replying normally.\nIf this run can complete the BOOTSTRAP.md workflow, do so.\nIf it cannot, explain the blocker briefly, continue with any bootstrap steps that are still possible here, and offer the simplest next step.\nDo not pretend bootstrap is complete when it is not.\nDo not use a generic first greeting or reply normally until after you have handled BOOTSTRAP.md.\nYour first user-visible reply for a bootstrap-pending workspace must follow BOOTSTRAP.md, not a generic greeting.\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"telegram:1477860192\",\n  \"message_id\": \"830\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1477860192\",\n  \"sender\": \"YuV\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Thu 2026-04-23 23:32 GMT+3\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"YuV (1477860192)\",\n  \"id\": \"1477860192\",\n  \"name\": \"YuV\",\n  \"username\": \"Discovery23\"\n}\n```\n\nТы Клодюр"}],"timestamp":1776976349134},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Considering user preferences**\n\nI think it's best not to use something too complex. I could offer some default options instead. Since the user is Russian, I wonder if I should consider crafting a response that’s concise and friendly in Russian. It feels important to match their preferences and comfort level. Overall, I'll work on creating a message that's straightforward and welcoming! Let's make sure it's easy to understand.","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_00cb66f64fbf78240069ea81df4d208192a7b3f8d87cdae42b\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp6oHk1yvJO-2BDUAK4QmR0NZG6IPZRjlPDGi1XHywlZ4Ndjr8z3VGn5dvQ0W527eEy5KwLi0AF6l4icwpj-H4Z66euYgV4ZOlXPnNvUCZiL6WMo3RhGxP78d5dROXEhnDTnxwA2BTLx7J6kt6eX9ZMFDTUMa3kJmLeY_wS8qRUJfxIAid40dIF1kFVoG91xcmGHEmDuGRF5OzB-n-iTp9Zv8a0w_tczrvc9whLL5ZjQ3PwrZs7PCo75wn9I9xqsF22odAi_Z_2WtguIg5OMwZtSdhItAk7mVJkyHJHpGm_SQrUEk2nazjnkQYZMUHkYB3Mp8sRMaF64CrkwAWkF8DyhET3SCfBMm1lF-3bnjIImCFgmdCZqhD2GpZhdr6G2FoV-7WZrIdrNUc2KqBo3soZW-DugfsbL48BYvCwMCvNdNNXSeLl_6bq1Cjb-EG87oLtdLB4y11tEfWrj26YGaUc3bBHFETlLWREaOxYLi_RUh99AniEQ7JO6cUOExfN-bKKTEzCjtB3Lc436Qbty30M7QPHvBwlSXefN8zijh124MaIr_fH-2o6kpxeRaAM3P3zeTk_AHkEyWIBml0HaVmjYcL030fD9IVLZ4JiZPGA6adX0fhv0Nl1KfQTqu4YV6mf0pJTQFQZQns8nwNKXfT3ovJWUffM5xot8LtYtZA0hH8dVihWlfhqG4lailuAVBYhW2PU6edkK5VMUoIkf8BO1StftjJiv6CAMmLWasCHFCLuZUyLscjknoG0OYOpi_yb-8Tt2lZ4pAqLdmEEnWlx1vqgkiOT_CiYYWAZ8C1m9pJP5oWSFroG5yX9ld-1QINdr2CPAjP73LA7qiV-QGlUP3aoXvoB_ZzYg4D6l2fTf-JPGJXknuf-R9KyP6OLJCbquUjx7ne