ting a local author for the repo. It feels like it might be destructive, but maybe it’s not. I’m considering using git config with my assistant identity. If I set the local git config with user.name \"Clodyur\" and user.email \"clodyur@local,\" would that be okay? I should probably verify that it's reversible before committing. Sounds like a plan!","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_00cb66f64fbf78240069ea822165908192a5948d279da37e36\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp6oIliFo_ufZTGJL8Iq5zUiRf56NkNaQsjj1o4e3QqWya35kribHtlxdWfWYbgT314vumz54wSiB3Uew6FvcGcCo2YH4p1ca95NpaDQNc3kXNDx5qoRt9O240EY7sry2hnyr4TCwAoO0WLreYpcasN87gfUo0netLUM8D-EhKdJ4M1CH74O51ro6wlMkiqZHkMXbzUocHLSH8oP2m-FxC_tUE_jaT_Tl7EMtt4VtoLVsScNzI9P6GpLMWVtzjpCecNWbVU2_0nKH-BQi-Eqe3IFv3iNmHJgszoU5hqEU-R8vl4_zjR2BUPIHLh2eEVXrQ9F4aNkwbDlM8HotHA_6zf0cZpVynZU0MhuyfwU3bmbUR9WmbX7g9RTZCblgmmKZ4YE5bTH_b7YRyYI67l5iEM1lZWbGBEQtqPafBsc1tfO0Mfg9Di3jIwKhU4kyIJiYaqinFGpoaXJDOrMcViSDgWxT3Dqh5-5gT06oTTpVzD0KBCmYrTzkWkNpf9Sa7EMYBWAmLnJ8054zXL8PtPPp07ug8iPP3h2kl5iRCyrn9XdyXbLp453ULun2_p3CdpS1rERdklGF8u2V7xQH7TTp4EX5HFs4cPHRhftLbarospAl7id4iCAajGVgJPx3fvJ-IFP5UuL3D4GpD1n1ItTxHajkqkb1hKn7-Rgh-Juj8ZbUK9PFRzr4DuGpbNr4h0NJutp1WY90FIi85JxhMhEDph-2apwlMi_wilTLvGlEQ6sLvQvGYkrOybLU2ZlPGeahwXIJ1v7AFB5nom2-_AMhK1RVbT9zoxzK6GRG2r0BLoJ9iI4vNFq-MMKH7DXEPxb7ZxATHjNG06xy4G636FgEagfj1dvtvegyYzz_554J0co1ae4eRcIAzc12d9uyDSMSIljQMdIYdXhSBvHtvP0NKWyhe4FFjKW_CDuL1-VCBRYT4cA4cykC0zzbearL90V955CbN5P6x8VVZhU8KvspuAhx225HG58Uhod3LQWGKpSwC8srR9hrTFWQumpDYwqVFzyOg0f8dl0EEbmWvaa5M9nyj6wg7CT4tCowdv8Zmehk_nlb4fk2StZcE28U7SolDTqhWXkprTGOib0Kem4Q4xRHm16azdqiaimARq4OF_YWuTTfsBXppaM-z4yPHNAp1V4rAHYAdM6roVtL8DHZuABUGRgb0jirkwIZNp79bjY3FSWKdNxOxrf-bo_QeirZpiLMQXEvporvQmSrzn48FXDjZ7RdGnZTyiaiLyCWrEIWDd9j_U9vYjSgFFrsxTnYMVKF4MmxYHRKqZCvvuRu6tAEvjgq5K76Qy1NGzPwUzWr1Mhhr3k5N5k8ofLjbboPyr3UlEtjnTLf_c0egHKAFklj5vDP6x7SpQM1wg4uh92g-iIU6vdKIUD44Mhlta047gya79e5awBu8jzslvWVvoG6v62eftHXuCTu0367gOdg_lCM=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating local commits**\\n\\nI need to briefly mention blockers. I think I could still commit locally by setting a local author for the repo. It feels like it might be destructive, but maybe it’s not. I’m considering using git config with my assistant identity. If I set the local git config with user.name \\\"Clodyur\\\" and user.email \\\"clodyur@local,\\\" would that be okay? I should probably verify that it's reversible before committing. Sounds like a plan!\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_J5z5iGmt9hNHTSgc5Cze5icS|fc_00cb66f64fbf78240069ea82250578819288b48f0c12a8a879","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"git config user.name \"Клодюр\" && git config user.email \"klodyur@local\" && git add IDENTITY.md USER.md && git commit -m \"Bootstrap identity defaults\"","workdir":"/home/yuri_artamonov/.openclaw/workspace","yieldMs":10000,"timeout":120},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"git config user.name \\\"Клодюр\\\" && git config user.email \\\"klodyur@local\\\" && git add IDENTITY.md USER.md && git commit -m \\\"Bootstrap identity defaults\\\"\",\"workdir\":\"/home/yuri_artamonov/.openclaw/workspace\",\"yieldMs\":10000,\"timeout\":120}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":323,"output":167,"cacheRead":14336,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14826,"cost":{"input":0.0008075000000000001,"output":0.002505,"cacheRead":0.003584,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0068965}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776976415533,"responseId":"resp_00cb66f64fbf78240069ea8220b7108192bd7855ad16af2901"},{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_J5z5iGmt9hNHTSgc5Cze5icS|fc_00cb66f64fbf78240069ea82250578819288b48f0c12a8a879","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[master (root-commit) d5114ea] Bootstrap identity defaults\n 2 files changed, 37 insertions(+)\n create mode 100644 IDENTITY.md\n create mode 100644 USER.md"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776976421653},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"","thinkingSignat