78240069ea82c1c8748192b0edf2655a982d55","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find . -maxdepth 3 -type f | sort","workdir":"/home/yuri_artamonov/.openclaw/workspace","yieldMs":10000,"timeout":120},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"find . -maxdepth 3 -type f | sort\",\"workdir\":\"/home/yuri_artamonov/.openclaw/workspace\",\"yieldMs\":10000,\"timeout\":120}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":872,"output":384,"cacheRead":15232,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":16488,"cost":{"input":0.00218,"output":0.00576,"cacheRead":0.0038079999999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.011748000000000001}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776976567544,"responseId":"resp_00cb66f64fbf78240069ea82b927308192b02b54579bc6d6d9"},{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_zeFHAkO8JRcR8aOkLsk7Fwa0|fc_00cb66f64fbf78240069ea82c1c8748192b0edf2655a982d55","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"./.git/COMMIT_EDITMSG\n./.git/HEAD\n./.git/config\n./.git/description\n./.git/hooks/applypatch-msg.sample\n./.git/hooks/commit-msg.sample\n./.git/hooks/fsmonitor-watchman.sample\n./.git/hooks/post-update.sample\n./.git/hooks/pre-applypatch.sample\n./.git/hooks/pre-commit.sample\n./.git/hooks/pre-merge-commit.sample\n./.git/hooks/pre-push.sample\n./.git/hooks/pre-rebase.sample\n./.git/hooks/pre-receive.sample\n./.git/hooks/prepare-commit-msg.sample\n./.git/hooks/push-to-checkout.sample\n./.git/hooks/sendemail-validate.sample\n./.git/hooks/update.sample\n./.git/index\n./.git/info/exclude\n./.git/logs/HEAD\n./.openclaw/workspace-state.json\n./AGENTS.md\n./HEARTBEAT.md\n./IDENTITY.md\n./SOUL.md\n./TOOLS.md\n./USER.md"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776976577995},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Planning workspace recovery**\n\nI need to mention that my inventory shows a clean workspace with only bootstrap files. Maybe I could ask if the user wants me to recreate specific skills or if I should commit anything? Since no actions have been taken, I might suggest a simple recovery plan: first, inventory what’s recoverable from the filesystem or backups; then, recreate necessary skills and documents; finally, harden everything with backups. I want to keep it easy, so I might say, \"I checked: the workspace is basically fresh; only identity/bootstrap files remain.\" I’m here to help!\n\n**Proposing next steps for recovery**\n\nSince the user hasn't asked a specific question, I can propose the next steps. They're tired, so I should keep it simple. Maybe I can suggest, \"What would you like to restore first: 1) skills, 2) documents/files, or 3) connections/stability?\" I could also offer to conduct a recovery audit to identify what’s left. It might be helpful to say, \"I see the workspace is almost empty, so let’s avoid guesswork.\" I think I should act now and search for old skills or backups without waiting for permission. That could truly help!\n\n**Considering recovery options**\n\nI’m thinking about what to recover first from the user's machine without going too deep into their files. I could search for recoverable remnants under home, but it might not be necessary to dig too much beyond the workspace. Since it’s their machine, I should prioritize a concise reply. I can say, \"Right now, we have a nearly clean environment,\" and then offer practical options and recommendations based on that. I want to ensure the user feels supported!","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_00cb66f64fbf78240069ea82c5292081928b225b4442d7a12c\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp6oLUeJmf-YEgBGLabIxHMvnqNoKgeixLmNl_605RDDES1dlE8I6rvJ6HIWDB8TV8K4ohzgJsnL7IkChF7HNmBGkNS8YFJUdNFQHJ0_OWjAemyVixiY50N_R0mwbD3LVX2nhN_OaTbG9jjeauFd4hRP69B1UUkXvax-TS2BaegbqDlpnGEoOVvh4yCOyWig2UYieqcBnGRqQMPDzjmdrioVr2PwrHLAkvui5Gu8ZKH9Dr0r_BWKNHvNvPshF_tw6thrp33oTZDOwLOViqrfSRiHEMCPeGmbmVEiBtdbcX6vsiFw-MFbFTWqWB5328mw8_RfVSjy4YrcC7OyrJRjQdj6sGYyHKahON63KfQ1s7JkRk1kZHWWr-t5kyjd97kL6IlindK7Q-Q-8D7qBEztwTn4jr1uESzt4AIxPiQOD6TeTRoXOEDj